      "message": "The external IPv6 subnet CIDR (PSB 2001:db8:0:1::/64) will be different to the tenant IPv6 subnet CIDR (2001:db8:0:2::20/64).\n\nBasically, IPv6 tenant subnets are expected to be Globally unique and routable. In OpenStack Neutron reference implementation we have following options. In ODL, we will be pursuing option1 currently.\n\nOption 1: Attach an external IPv6 subnet and explicitly specify the upstream router IPv6 Link Local Address (LLA) as gateway\n\nAttachment of an IPv6 subnet to an external network is optional in case of IPv6 since we can use the IPv6 LLA of the router-gateway-port for forwarding and also because the tenant subnets are already Globally Unique: So, there are two additional options.\nOption 2: The neutron router can learn the IPv6 address of external gateway by processing the Router Advertisement (RA) messages from the external gateway.\nOption 3: Manual configuration of IPv6 LLA address of external gateway in the /etc/neutron/l3-agent.ini file",
